text.section:
The powers granted to any municipal corporation pursuant to this section shall not be construed:
To grant to such municipality powers in any substantive area not otherwise granted to such municipality by other public general or public local law;
To restrict such municipality from exercising any power granted to such municipality by other public general or public local law or otherwise;
To authorize such municipality or its officers to engage in any activity which is beyond their power under other public general law, public local law, or otherwise; or
To preempt or supersede the regulatory authority of any State department or agency under any public general law.
